---
description: Rules for Vue component development
globs: "**/*.vue"
---

# Component Structure
- One component should have one clear responsibility
- Keep components small and focused
- Split component only when necessary (reuse or too large)

# Template
- Keep template simple and readable
- Avoid complex inline expressions
- Move logic to script section when possible

# Script (TypeScript)
- Use simple and clear types
- Avoid complex generics
- Prefer explicit typing when helpful
- Do not over-abstract types

# Props & State
- Keep props minimal and well-defined
- Avoid passing unnecessary data
- Use computed for derived state
- Do not duplicate state

# Events
- Keep event naming consistent
- Avoid excessive event chaining

# Styling
- Prefer simple class usage
- Avoid complex dynamic styling logic
- Use scoped styles when appropriate

# Constraints
- Do not rewrite entire component
- Do not restructure component unless required
- Only modify relevant parts